data.text: South Korea or Republic of Korea is located on the Korean Peninsula in East Asia. South Korea has borders with North Korea to the North, the Sea of Japan to the East and the Yellow Sea to the West. The capital of South Korea is Seoul, which is situated in the North West of the nation. Seoul is one of the big finance capital of Aisa, and it has Asia third largest stock exchange. Seoul is also home to the head quarters of Samsung. South Korea is also in the G20 as it is the worlds fifteenth largest economy.
